gomodel:SYNGO_885  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper elegantly characterized the role of calbindin as a Ca2+ buffer at the presynaptic compartment of multipolar bursting interneurons in the mouse neocortex. Paired whole cell recordings of presynaptic interneurons synapsing on pyramidal cells in layer 2/3 were made.\nIn WT pairs, paired-pulse facilitation of the IPSPs is seen when two depolarizations are given with a 10 Hz frequency (Fig 2A left). After a long recordings, the first IPSC is increased in amplitude and the PPF is reduced (Figure 2A right and 2B left).\nIn calbindin KOs, the first IPSC amplitude is increased already at the start of the recordings, the initial PPF is reduced (2C left and 2B right), and there is no change following long recordings (2B left).\nThese data suggest that in WT cells, a Ca2+ buffer in the presynapse limits the size of the first IPSC and leads to a strong PPF. During the long recordings the buffer is washed out into the recording electrode, the first IPSC amplitudes increases in size and the PPF is reduced.\nFigure 2C (right) shows that calbindin loading in the presynaptic compartment of the knockout interneuron reduces the amplitude of first IPSP and restores facilitation. There is little effect of the loading in WT synapses.\nFigure 3 A and B show similar effects on the initial IPSC amplitude and on the PPR when loading a WT terminal where the endogenous Ca2+ buffer has been washed out with the fast Ca2+-buffer BAPTA.\nTaken together, these data demonstrate a role for calbindin as a Ca2+ buffer regulating presynaptic Ca2+ concentrations, basal release probability and short-term synaptic plasticity at the presynapse of interneurons.\n\nIn figure 5 and 6 similar effects are documented in CA3 mossy fiber calbindin KO synapses.. Experimental description: 'Electrophysiology: hippocampal slices of 250 μm thickness were prepared from the brains of 14-day-old C57Bl6 and CB knockout (Klapstein et al. 1998) mice killed by decapitation.'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-07-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_885" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

